##After working in the isolation ward, I went back to the factory to help get back to work

Micro Signal Xinminzhoukan

Function description, depth and angle —— this is what we can do.

Working in a factory is completely different from working in a hospital, and I've never done this kind of work before, so when I first came here, I was just feeling my way through the river. I have found that the first step is to mingle with the workers, to become their friends, and then to better promote professional medical knowledge.

Dictation | Ma Xiaofei

To clean up the mess

February 27th was the tenth day of Quarantine at the hotel after I finished my work in the isolation ward. That afternoon, I received a notice from the hospital that I wouldn't have to work in the isolation ward after the quarantine period was over because the outbreak was under control.

Upon hearing the news, I immediately called my family and told them the good news that I was going to "unseal" and that the family would be reunited soon. They haven't seen me for almost a month, and I'm a little worried about them, and I'd like to go home. Unexpectedly, the next day, the hospital called and said, we have key enterprises in Jingzhou to resume production, have to arrange in-plant medical staff to help enterprises, do a good job in epidemic prevention and control and medical security. They wanted me to go and ask me if I was having any trouble.

After a few seconds of hesitation, I said, almost instinctively, "no problem, take it under advisement. " Then I spoke to my family, who were somewhat disappointed. Because the first day on the phone, I told them they could go home, and they started cleaning my room.

Now, I've been working in this closed factory for 11 days. I haven't been home in almost 40 days since I left on February 2nd.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Ma Xiaofei was in isolation ward

From treating patients to helping workers

My name is Ma Xiaofei, Hubei Jingzhou Hospital of Traditional Chinese medicine, an associate director of Orthopedic Physicians. Before this, because of the outbreak, I as an orthopedic Doctor, also received to fight the epidemic front notice.

February 2nd, before I went into quarantine, I was, to be honest, a little nervous and anxious. On the one hand may be a professional relationship, understanding and access to more relevant information, know that the disease is highly contagious, and temporarily no targeted drugs; on the other hand, the epidemic was still developing at that time, the situation is also more serious. Before I left home, I thought about writing down my bank card number, my pin number, everything. On second thought, no need. My wife was in charge of the economy.

But by the time I started working with colleagues, the tension had faded. I was assigned to the sixth ward of Jingzhou Hospital of Traditional Chinese medicine. Our Ward mainly receives the light case new coronary pneumonia to diagnose the patient. In the course of daily diagnosis and treatment, I found that most of the patients in the ward had more or less psychological obstacles, some felt that they had lost their freedom and did not cooperate with the isolation treatment, some did not want to face their illness, some were pessimistic and misanthropic, who has their own online search for a treatment plan that requires a doctor to compare it.

So, in addition to regular therapy, I spend most of my time in each class trying to calm and soothe my patients. Which is why Dr. Trudo said, "sometimes it heals, sometimes it helps, sometimes it comforts. " .

When I went into the quarantine zone, it was the height of the epidemic. There are 14 isolation wards in our ward, and at the worst they are full. We are a traditional Chinese Medicine Hospital, so every day will collect each patient's pulse, tongue coating, reported to the hospital expert group, by them to give personalized Chinese medicine treatment. Such a treatment program, follow-up seems to be a good effect.

As a result of the Hainan medical team to help us, so to February 17,15 consecutive days of work I ended the first phase of work, began to take leave. When we left the hospital, things were not as good as they are now, and the number of patients was not significantly reduced, so the leaders told us to prepare ourselves for the possibility of a new front.

Then came the quarantine at the hotel. On February 27th the hospital told me that the number of quarantined wards had been reduced from six to three, and that doctors on leave were no longer needed. I thought that after a few days can go home, the next day received to the factory to help resume production task.

Although just received the phone call I hesitated, but after making a call, I think this new task is quite suitable for me, after all, I just came from the front line of the fight against the epidemic, accumulated a lot of experience to help enterprises do a good job of epidemic prevention and control. On the night of the 29th, I arrived at the factory. This is the auto parts factory of a local french-owned Company in Jingzhou.

One of the things that happened that night made me feel like I was right. It turned out that the day before the factory a couple back to work, which, the female worker cough more severe, her husband also has a bit of diarrhea. Whether they themselves, or other workers, in this special period, in the face of this situation, people are scared, grass and trees.

The couple had gone to the hospital for a checkup before my nurse partner and I arrived at the factory. Neither of them had the new coronavirus. The woman had pneumonia. But when they came back, they were still very nervous, always worried that they would be misdiagnosed, and there were many rumors in the factory that they were suspected patients of new crown pneumonia. When I learned this, I had a face-to-face conversation with them in the office.

I told them, "don't worry about it. I've seen the test results. It's not a big deal. ". If you're really infected, I can't sit here and talk to you this close. The couple laughed when they heard that. I remember we talked for quite a while that day, for more than half an hour, and when we parted, it was clear that they were in much better spirits. Later, the other workers were relieved to see that we had spent so much time together in the room.

It also epitomized my recent assistance in returning to work and production. Working in a factory is completely different from working in a hospital, and I've never done this kind of work before, so when I first came here, I was just feeling my way through the river. I have found that the first step is to mingle with the workers, to become their friends, and then to better promote professional medical knowledge.

In addition, while doing a good job of epidemic prevention and control, but not due to excessive epidemic prevention and the formation of a tense atmosphere, after all, our work in addition to epidemic prevention, more important is to help enterprises smoothly resume production.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
To extend local epidemic prevention experience to global factories

I've been in the factory for the last 10 days. In addition to completing the daily work, also summarizes some related experience. For example, we designed a set of test questions, 30% about safe return to work, 70% about new pneumonia itself. Now workers returning to the factory, after our popular science, but also through this examination to take up their posts.

In addition, because workers are generally young, usually after work if they feel energetic, workers like to visit each other. But at this particular time, it's something that needs to be avoided. So we introduced to you through the Wechat Group of our traditional Chinese medicine characteristics of the Baduanjin, so that after work in the dormitory workers can be self-entertainment, send off the exuberant energy, but also exercise.

I'm currently on call at the factory 24 hours a day, and workers can come to me whenever they need health advice. In addition to our medical staff, the factory is also equipped with a special drug procurement staff. On the premise of ensuring safety, the efficiency of medical treatment for workers has been greatly improved. Now is a special period, the whole city closed management, workers if they want to go out to see a doctor, neither convenient, nor safe.

What I didn't expect was that these experiences would one day be replicated in factories in other countries. As mentioned above, this is a factory owned by a french-owned Enterprise. Recently, with the outbreak of the global epidemic, the company's factories in other countries also face prevention and control problems. So, one day when I was talking with the relevant person in charge of the factory, it occurred to me that we could generalize our practice during this period.

Now the factory is almost 30% of the resumption rate, and when almost full resumption of work, I can go home. When I get home, I'm GonNa Tell my family I'm sorry. Because as a doctor, I feel that I have given a satisfactory answer to the test of the epidemic. But as a husband, father, son, it should be a fail... Then, I guess there is no vacation, I have a lot of old patients waiting for me, I continue to put on my white coat to go to work!
